sec.p:
Pressure distribution of the air film is very sensitive to the boundary conditions. In order to facilitate theoretical analysis, a representative region, consisting of a circular porous medium (0  <  r  <  R1) and an annular flange (R1  <  r  <  R2), is selected, as shown in Figure 2. A cylinder coordinate system is built with the centre of the porous surface as the origin point, and, the transverse and radial coordinates are z and r, respectively. Owing to the complexity of flowing in the gap formed by the flying workpiece and the porous wall, the following assumptions are made to enable a theoretical modelling:


airflow in the gap is laminar, dominated by viscous effects;

air state change remains isothermal (room temperature);

pressure distribution in z-direction is negligible;

inner geometry of the porous medium, the surface as well, is isotropic and homogeneous; and

the boundaries of the representative region are open to environments (atmospheric pressure).

Figure 2.
Airflow model: (a) representative region; (b) radial flow in the gap.
